The paper deals with join processing, which is a fundamental problem in database systems, and proposes algorithms for generating box covers and domain orderings to optimize the performance of join algorithms. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The paper also involves geometric algorithms and data structures, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely category. The paper mentions NP-hardness and approximation algorithms, indicating cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses the geometric framework for joins, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible category.
